# DATA_SCOPE.md

## Purpose

Define data classes and handling rules for {{ project.name }}.

## Data Classes

| data class | allowed | storage | notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| public or synthetic fixture | yes | repository allowed | Preferred for tests and examples |
| private input | restricted | repository prohibited | Summarize only when needed |
| generated output | conditional | target folder only | Review before commit |
| secrets | no | repository prohibited | Never store secrets |
| live configuration | no | repository prohibited | Keep outside repo |

## Rules

- Use synthetic fixtures for examples.
- Do not store private input in the repository.
- Do not store secrets, account values, or live configuration.
- Do not include equipment connection details or live parameters.

## Review Checklist

- Private input absent.
- Secrets absent.
- Live config absent.
- Generated output reviewed.
